{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"completed","call_id":"tool_866fefe6-a0a7-4d25-8fcd-151d2412bd9","tool_call":{"mcpToolCall":{"args":{"name":"context7-query-docs","args":{"libraryId":"/websites/orm_drizzle_team","query":"pgEnum pgTable uniqueIndex partial index where clause onConflictDoUpdate onConflictDoNothing foreign key references"},"toolCallId":"tool_866fefe6-a0a7-4d25-8fcd-151d2412bd9","providerIdentifier":"context7","toolName":"query-docs","smartModeApprovalOnly":false,"skipApproval":false},"result":{"success":{"content":[{"text":{"text":"### Declare Enum and Tables with Indexes and Foreign Keys\n\nSource: https://orm.drizzle.team/docs/latest-releases/drizzle-orm-v0110\n\nDemonstrates how to declare a custom enum type and define PostgreSQL tables with serial primary keys, varchar columns, unique indexes, foreign key constraints, and enum columns.\n\n```typescript\nexport const popularityEnum = createEnum({ alias: 'popularity', values: ['unknown', 'known', 'popular'] });\n\nexport class CountriesTable extends PgTable<CountriesTable> {\n  id = this.serial(\"id\").primaryKey();\n  name = this.varchar(\"name\", { size: 256 })\n\n  // declaring index\n  nameIndex = this.uniqueIndex(this.name)\n\n  public tableName(): string {\n    return 'countries';\n  }\n}\n\nexport class CitiesTable extends PgTable<CitiesTable> {\n  id = this.serial(\"id\").primaryKey();\n  name = this.varchar(\"name\", { size: 256 })\n  countryId = this.int(\"country_id\").foreignKey(CountriesTable, (country) => country.id)\n\n  // declaring enum column in table\n  popularity = this.type(popularityEnum, \"popularity\")\n\n  public tableName(): string {\n    return 'cities';\n  }\n}\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Upsert with onConflictDoUpdate in PostgreSQL\n\nSource: https://orm.drizzle.team/docs/guides/upsert\n\nDemonstrates how to use the `onConflictDoUpdate` method for upsert operations in PostgreSQL. This is useful when you want to update an existing record if a conflict occurs on a specified constraint, otherwise insert a new record.\n\n```typescript\nimport { pgTable, serial, text, uniqueIndex, sql } from \"drizzle-orm/pg-core\";\nimport { drizzle } from \"drizzle-orm/node-postgres\";\nimport { Client } from \"pg\";\n\nconst client = new Client({\n  connectionString: \"postgres://username:password@host:port/database\",\n});\nawait client.connect();\n\nconst db = drizzle(client);\n\nconst users = pgTable(\n  \"users\",\n  {\n    id: serial(\"id\").primaryKey(),\n    name: text(\"name\").notNull(),\n    email: text(\"email\").notNull(),\n    count: serial(\"count\"),\n  },\n  (users) => ({\n    emailIndex: uniqueIndex(\"email_idx\").on(users.email),\n  })\n);\n\n// Insert a new user or update if email already exists\nawait db\n  .insert(users)\n  .values({ name: \"John Doe\", email: \"john.doe@example.com\" })\n  .onConflictDoUpdate({\n    target: users.email,\n    set: {\n      name: \"John Doe Updated\",\n      count: sql`${users.count} + 1`\n    },\n  });\n\n// Insert a new user or update if id already exists\nawait db\n  .insert(users)\n  .values({ id: 1, name: \"Jane Doe\", email: \"jane.doe@example.com\" })\n  .onConflictDoUpdate({\n    target: users.id,\n    set: {\n      name: \"Jane Doe Updated\",\n      count: sql`${users.count} + 1`\n    },\n  });\n\nawait client.end();\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Upsert with `WHERE` Clause (PostgreSQL/SQLite)\n\nSource: https://orm.drizzle.team/docs/guides/upsert\n\nUse the `setWhere` option within `.onConflictDoUpdate()` to conditionally update rows. The update only occurs if the condition specified in `setWhere` is met.\n\n```typescript\nimport { or, sql } from 'drizzle-orm';\nimport { products } from './schema';\n\nconst data = {\n  id: 1,\n  title: 'Phone',\n  price: '999.99',\n  stock: 10,\n  lastUpdated: new Date(),\n};\n\nconst excludedPrice = sql.raw(`excluded.${products.price.name}`);\nconst excludedStock = sql.raw(`excluded.${products.stock.name}`);\n\nawait db\n  .insert(products)\n  .values(data)\n  .onConflictDoUpdate({\n    target: products.id,\n    set: {\n      price: excludedPrice,\n      stock: excludedStock,\n    },\n    setWhere: or(\n      sql`${products.stock}::integer > 0`,\n      sql`${products.stock}::integer = 0 AND excluded.${products.stock.name}::integer > 0`\n    ),\n  });\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Insert with On Conflict Do Update on Composite Index\n\nSource: https://orm.drizzle.team/docs/insert\n\nHandle conflicts on composite indexes or primary keys using `onConflictDoUpdate` by providing an array of columns as the target.\n\n```typescript\nawait db.insert(users)\n  .values({ firstName: 'John', lastName: 'Doe' })\n  .onConflictDoUpdate({\n    target: [users.firstName, users.lastName],\n    set: { firstName: 'John1' }\n  });\n```\n\n### Insert > On conflict do update\n\nSource: https://orm.drizzle.team/docs/insert\n\nThe `onConflictDoUpdate` method updates the row if a conflict occurs. It supports specifying a target for the conflict and a `set` clause for the update. Additionally, `where` clauses can be used to define conditions for partial indexes (`targetWhere`) or for the update itself (`setWhere`). This method also supports composite indexes or primary keys for conflict targets."}}],"isError":false}}},"hookAdditionalContexts":[],"toolCallId":"tool_866fefe6-a0a7-4d25-8fcd-151d2412bd9","startedAtMs":"1782957256611","completedAtMs":"1782957261799"},"model_call_id":"5977d0c1-3ad5-42be-85f2-1e8828435224-5-sc5c","session_id":"6573c6ff-6012-4c40-8cb2-1911b390dd96","timestamp_ms":1782957261766}
{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"completed","call_id":"tool_f8df602a-1c1d-466e-9926-e55e302358e","tool_call":{"mcpToolCall":{"args":{"name":"context7-query-docs","args":{"libraryId":"/websites/tanstack_start","query":"createServerFn inputValidator middleware createMiddleware zod validation"},"toolCallId":"tool_f8df602a-1c1d-466e-9926-e55e302358e","providerIdentifier":"context7","toolName":"query-docs","smartModeApprovalOnly":false,"skipApproval":false},"result":{"success":{"content":[{"text":{"text":"### Validate Server Function Parameters with Zod Schema (TypeScript)\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/server-functions.md\n\nIntegrate Zod for robust schema-based validation of server function input data, ensuring type safety and data integrity.\n\n```tsx\nimport { createServerFn } from '@tanstack/react-start'\nimport { z } from 'zod'\n\nconst UserSchema = z.object({\n  name: z.string().min(1),\n  age: z.number().min(0),\n})\n\nexport const createUser = createServerFn({ method: 'POST' })\n  .validator(UserSchema)\n  .handler(async ({ data }) => {\n    // data is fully typed and validated\n    return `Created user: ${data.name}, age ${data.age}`\n  })\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Validate User Input with Zod in TypeScript\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/authentication.md\n\nIllustrates how to use Zod for robust input validation on a server function. Defines a schema for email and password, ensuring data integrity before processing.\n\n```tsx\nimport { z } from 'zod'\n\nconst loginSchema = z.object({\n  email: z.string().email().max(255),\n  password: z.string().min(8).max(100)\n})\n\nexport const loginFn = createServerFn({ method: 'POST' })\n  .validator((data) => loginSchema.parse(data))\n  .handler(async ({ data }) => {\n    // data is now validated\n  })\n\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Validating Data with .validator Method and Zod\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/middleware.md\n\nDemonstrates using the `.validator` method with `zod` to validate and potentially modify the input data before it reaches the server function.\n\n```tsx\nimport { createMiddleware } from '@tanstack/react-start'\nimport { zodValidator } from '@tanstack/zod-adapter'\nimport { z } from 'zod'\n\nconst mySchema = z.object({\n  workspaceId: z.string(),\n})\n\nconst workspaceMiddleware = createMiddleware({ type: 'function' })\n  .validator(zodValidator(mySchema))\n  .server(({ next, data }) => {\n    console.log('Workspace ID:', data.workspaceId)\n    return next()\n  })\n```\n\n### Parameters & Validation > Validation with Zod\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/server-functions.md\n\nFor robust data validation in server functions, schema libraries like Zod can be used. Zod allows defining schemas for input data, ensuring it is fully typed and validated before processing.\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Server Function Middleware > The .validator method\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/middleware.md\n\nThe `.validator` method is used to modify and validate the data object before it reaches the current middleware, any nested middleware, and the final server function. It expects a function that processes the data, often utilizing validation libraries like `zod`."}}],"isError":false}}},"hookAdditionalContexts":[],"toolCallId":"tool_f8df602a-1c1d-466e-9926-e55e302358e","startedAtMs":"1782957257087","completedAtMs":"1782957263371"},"model_call_id":"5977d0c1-3ad5-42be-85f2-1e8828435224-5-sc5c","session_id":"6573c6ff-6012-4c40-8cb2-1911b390dd96","timestamp_ms":1782957263346}
