{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"completed","call_id":"tool_6ce9b27b-f59e-4788-a359-7f66cea5955","tool_call":{"mcpToolCall":{"args":{"name":"context7-query-docs","args":{"libraryId":"/websites/tanstack_start","query":"createMiddleware server next context handler access middleware context in server function"},"toolCallId":"tool_6ce9b27b-f59e-4788-a359-7f66cea5955","providerIdentifier":"context7","toolName":"query-docs","smartModeApprovalOnly":false,"skipApproval":false},"result":{"success":{"content":[{"text":{"text":"### Providing Server-Side Context to Next Middleware (TypeScript)\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/middleware.md\n\nUse the `next` function with a `context` property to merge data into the parent context, making it available to subsequent server middleware.\n\n```tsx\nimport { createMiddleware } from '@tanstack/react-start'\n\nconst awesomeMiddleware = createMiddleware({ type: 'function' }).server(\n  ({ next }) => {\n    return next({\n      context: {\n        isAwesome: Math.random() > 0.5,\n      },\n    })\n  },\n)\n\nconst loggingMiddleware = createMiddleware({ type: 'function' })\n  .middleware([awesomeMiddleware])\n  .server(async ({ next, context }) => {\n    console.log('Is awesome?', context.isAwesome)\n    return next()\n  })\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Accessing `next`, `context`, and `request` in Middleware Server Method\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/middleware.md\n\nDemonstrates how the `.server` method of a middleware receives `next`, `context`, and `request` objects, allowing for interaction with the middleware chain and request details.\n\n```tsx\nimport { createMiddleware } from '@tanstack/react-start'\n\nconst loggingMiddleware = createMiddleware().server(\n  ({ next, context, request }) => {\n    return next()\n  },\n)\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Apply Authentication Middleware to Server Function (TypeScript)\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/authentication-server-primitives.md\n\nAttach the `authMiddleware` to any server function that requires an authenticated session. The handler will then have access to the session object via its context.\n\n```typescript\nimport { createServerFn } from '@tanstack/react-start'\nimport { authMiddleware } from '~/server/auth-middleware'\n\nexport const getMyOrders = createServerFn({ method: 'GET' })\n  .middleware([authMiddleware])\n  .handler(async ({ context }) => {\n    return db.orders.findMany({ where: { userId: context.session.userId } })\n  })\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Create Authentication Middleware (TypeScript)\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/authentication-server-primitives.md\n\nUse this middleware to centralize session loading and ensure every protected server handler receives a typed session context. It reads a session token and throws an error if the session is invalid or unauthorized.\n\n```typescript\n// src/server/auth-middleware.ts\nimport { createMiddleware } from '@tanstack/react-start'\nimport { readSessionToken } from './session'\n\nexport const authMiddleware = createMiddleware({ type: 'function' }).server(\n  async ({ next }) => {\n    const token = readSessionToken()\n    const session = token ? await db.sessions.findValid(token) : null\n    if (!session) throw new Error('Unauthorized')\n    return next({ context: { session } })\n  },\n)\n```\n\n### Context Management > Providing Context via `next`\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/middleware.md\n\nThe `next` function in middleware can be called with an object containing a `context` property. Any properties passed to this `context` value will be merged into the parent context and made available to the next middleware in the chain."}}],"isError":false}}},"hookAdditionalContexts":[],"toolCallId":"tool_6ce9b27b-f59e-4788-a359-7f66cea5955","startedAtMs":"1782957490529","completedAtMs":"1782957495860"},"model_call_id":"5977d0c1-3ad5-42be-85f2-1e8828435224-20-bxxo","session_id":"6573c6ff-6012-4c40-8cb2-1911b390dd96","timestamp_ms":1782957495838}
