{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"started","call_id":"tool_f1639afb-a327-4e0b-98ef-bb263274906","tool_call":{"mcpToolCall":{"args":{"name":"context7-query-docs","args":{"libraryId":"/websites/tanstack_start","query":"createFileRoute loader server function fetch data in route component"},"toolCallId":"tool_f1639afb-a327-4e0b-98ef-bb263274906","providerIdentifier":"context7","toolName":"query-docs","smartModeApprovalOnly":false,"skipApproval":false}},"hookAdditionalContexts":[],"toolCallId":"tool_f1639afb-a327-4e0b-98ef-bb263274906","startedAtMs":"1782957627071"},"model_call_id":"5977d0c1-3ad5-42be-85f2-1e8828435224-26-v4nl","session_id":"6573c6ff-6012-4c40-8cb2-1911b390dd96","timestamp_ms":1782957627050}
{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"completed","call_id":"tool_f1639afb-a327-4e0b-98ef-bb263274906","tool_call":{"mcpToolCall":{"args":{"name":"context7-query-docs","args":{"libraryId":"/websites/tanstack_start","query":"createFileRoute loader server function fetch data in route component"},"toolCallId":"tool_f1639afb-a327-4e0b-98ef-bb263274906","providerIdentifier":"context7","toolName":"query-docs","smartModeApprovalOnly":false,"skipApproval":false},"result":{"success":{"content":[{"text":{"text":"### Call Server Functions from Route Loaders and React Components\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/server-functions.md\n\nServer functions can be invoked within route loaders for data fetching or from React components using the `useServerFn()` hook for client-side interactions.\n\n```tsx\n// In a route loader\nexport const Route = createFileRoute('/posts')({\n  loader: () => getServerPosts(),\n})\n\n// In a component\nfunction PostList() {\n  const getPosts = useServerFn(getServerPosts)\n\n  const { data } = useQuery({\n    queryKey: ['posts'],\n    queryFn: () => getPosts(),\n  })\n}\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Refactor Data Fetching from Next.js to TanStack Start Loader\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/migrate-from-next-js.md\n\nThis snippet demonstrates how to migrate data fetching from a Next.js `async` component to TanStack Start's `createFileRoute` with a `loader` function and `useLoaderData` hook for improved data management.\n\n```tsx\n- export default async function Page() { // [!code --]\n+ export const Route = createFileRoute('/')({ // [!code ++]\n+   component: Page, // [!code ++]\n+   loader: async () => { // [!code ++]\n+     const res = await fetch('https://api.vercel.app/blog') // [!code ++]\n+     return res.json() // [!code ++]\n+   }, // [!code ++]\n+ }) // [!code ++]\n\n+ function Page() { // [!code ++]\n-   const data = await fetch('https://api.vercel.app/blog') // [!code --]\n-   const posts = await data.json() // [!code --]\n+   const posts = Route.useLoaderData() // [!code ++]\n\n  return (\n    <ul>\n      {posts.map((post) => (\n        <li key={post.id}>{post.title}</li>\n      ))}\n    </ul>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Create React Route with Server-Side API Fetch\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/tutorial/fetching-external-api.md\n\nDefine a React route that uses `createServerFn` to securely fetch popular movie data from the TMDB API on the server, preventing exposure of API credentials to the client.\n\n```typescript\n// src/routes/fetch-movies.tsx\nimport { createFileRoute } from '@tanstack/react-router'\nimport type { Movie, TMDBResponse } from '../types/movie'\nimport { createServerFn } from '@tanstack/react-start'\n\nconst API_URL =\n  'https://api.themoviedb.org/3/discover/movie?include_adult=false&include_video=false&language=en-US&page=1&sort_by=popularity.desc'\n\nconst fetchPopularMovies = createServerFn().handler(\n  async (): Promise<TMDBResponse> => {\n    const response = await fetch(API_URL, {\n      headers: {\n        accept: 'application/json',\n        Authorization: `Bearer ${process.env.TMDB_AUTH_TOKEN}`,\n      },\n    })\n\n    if (!response.ok) {\n      throw new Error(`Failed to fetch movies: ${response.statusText}`)\n    }\n\n    return response.json()\n  },\n)\n\nexport const Route = createFileRoute('/fetch-movies')({\n  component: MoviesPage,\n  loader: async (): Promise<{ movies: Movie[]; error: string | null }> => {\n    try {\n      const moviesData = await fetchPopularMovies()\n      return { movies: moviesData.results, error: null }\n    } catch (error) {\n      console.error('Error fetching movies:', error)\n      return { movies: [], error: 'Failed to load movies' }\n    }\n  }\n})\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Fetch Multiple Server Components in Parallel using `Promise.all`\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/guide/server-components.md\n\nFetch several independent server components concurrently using `Promise.all` within the route loader when components have separate data sources and no shared dependencies.\n\n```tsx\nconst getArticleA = createServerFn().handler(async () => {\n  const article = await db.articles.findById('a')\n  return renderServerComponent(<Article data={article} />)\n})\n\nconst getArticleB = createServerFn().handler(async () => {\n  const article = await db.articles.findById('b')\n  return renderServerComponent(<Article data={article} />)\n})\n\nconst getSidebar = createServerFn().handler(async () => {\n  const trending = await db.articles.getTrending()\n  return renderServerComponent(<Sidebar items={trending} />)\n})\n\nexport const Route = createFileRoute('/news')({\n  loader: async () => {\n    const [ArticleA, ArticleB, Sidebar] = await Promise.all([\n      getArticleA(),\n      getArticleB(),\n      getSidebar(),\n    ])\n    return { ArticleA, ArticleB, Sidebar }\n  },\n  component: NewsPage,\n})\n\nfunction NewsPage() {\n  const { ArticleA, ArticleB, Sidebar } = Route.useLoaderData()\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"grid\">\n      <main>\n        {ArticleA}\n        {ArticleB}\n      </main>\n      <aside>{Sidebar}</aside>\n    </div>\n  )\n}\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Consume Jokes Server Function in Route (JSX)\n\nSource: https://tanstack.com/start/latest/docs/framework/react/tutorial/reading-writing-file.md\n\nUse this code in `src/routes/index.tsx` to define the root route, load jokes data using `getJokes` via TanStack Router's loader, and pass it to the `JokesList` component.\n\n```jsx\n// src/routes/index.tsx\nimport { createFileRoute } from '@tanstack/react-router'\nimport { getJokes } from './serverActions/jokesActions'\nimport { JokesList } from './JokesList'\n\nexport const Route = createFileRoute('/')({\n  loader: async () => {\n    // Load jokes data when the route is accessed\n    return getJokes()\n  },\n  component: App,\n})\n\nconst App = () => {\n  const jokes = Route.useLoaderData() || []\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-12 px-4 space-y-6\">\n      <h1 className=\"text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-10\">DevJokes</h1>\n      <JokesList jokes={jokes} />\n    </div>\n  )\n}\n```"}}],"isError":false}}},"hookAdditionalContexts":[],"toolCallId":"tool_f1639afb-a327-4e0b-98ef-bb263274906","startedAtMs":"1782957627071","completedAtMs":"1782957632480"},"model_call_id":"5977d0c1-3ad5-42be-85f2-1e8828435224-26-v4nl","session_id":"6573c6ff-6012-4c40-8cb2-1911b390dd96","timestamp_ms":1782957632463}
